snippet.textDisplay: Honestly, I think this hits me in a different way. When I was battling cancer and after I've been in remission, I was alone. Asides from my mom and dad, fiance. I had friends who never cared. I had some family who never cared to show up or ever contact me.  Now that I've been in 9 months remission I still feel lonely and I know im not alone.  I know I have people who care for me and love me. But after cancer, it ruined my life. I never got to experience my life at 18 and 19.  I'm disabled now due to my tumor on my spinal cord.  But honestly this hit home.
